cs.LG, cs.AR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.ET 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category as it proposes a new technique using deep reinforcement learning to address the phase-ordering problem. It may also belong to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) as it focuses on optimizing the code generated by the front-end compiler for high-level synthesis. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it evaluates the performance of the LLVM compiler and compares it to state-of-the-art algorithms. It may also fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages) as it deals with optimizing the order in which optimization passes are applied. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) as it proposes a new technique for addressing a challenging problem in high-level synthesis.
